<dec f='include/libavcodec/avcodec.h' l='4333' type='int avcodec_close(AVCodecContext * avctx)'/>
<doc f='include/libavcodec/avcodec.h' l='4320'>/**
 * Close a given AVCodecContext and free all the data associated with it
 * (but not the AVCodecContext itself).
 *
 * Calling this function on an AVCodecContext that hasn&apos;t been opened will free
 * the codec-specific data allocated in avcodec_alloc_context3() with a non-NULL
 * codec. Subsequent calls will do nothing.
 *
 * @note Do not use this function. Use avcodec_free_context() to destroy a
 * codec context (either open or closed). Opening and closing a codec context
 * multiple times is not supported anymore -- use multiple codec contexts
 * instead.
 */</doc>
